---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import Icon from '../../../components/Icon.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Why do historic homes need specialized cleaning?",
    answer: "Twickenham's antebellum and historic homes feature original hardwood floors, period millwork, plaster walls, antique fixtures, and irreplaceable architectural details. Modern harsh chemicals can damage these surfaces permanently. We use pH-balanced, preservation-safe products and techniques specifically designed for historic properties. Our team understands the difference between cleaning and conserving."
  },
  {
    question: "How do you protect original hardwood floors?",
    answer: "Historic hardwood requires special care - no steam cleaning, no harsh chemicals, no excessive water. We use microfiber systems and wood-safe cleaners that clean effectively without damaging original finishes. For floors with historic varnish or oil finishes, we adjust our methods accordingly. We've cleaned dozens of Twickenham homes and understand these floors are irreplaceable investments."
  },
  {
    question: "Can you clean around antiques and period furnishings?",
    answer: "Absolutely. Many Twickenham homes contain museum-quality antiques, period furniture, and family heirlooms. Our team is trained in proper handling - we use lint-free cloths, appropriate products for different materials, and gentle techniques. We never move valuable items without permission and communicate about any concerns. Your treasures are safe with us."
  },
  {
    question: "What about plaster walls and delicate moldings?",
    answer: "Plaster walls and historic millwork require a soft touch. We use appropriate products that won't damage painted plaster or strip historic finishes. For crown moldings, baseboards, and detailed woodwork, we hand-clean with care rather than using aggressive methods. We understand these details define your home's historic character and treat them accordingly."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you understand historic preservation standards?",
    answer: "Yes. Twickenham is a National Register Historic District, and we've worked in dozens of homes here. We understand Secretary of the Interior Standards and the importance of preserving original materials. Whether your home is a documented antebellum house or a contributing historic structure, we clean with preservation principles in mind - maintaining character-defining features while achieving modern cleanliness standards."
  },
  {
    question: "How do you handle high ceilings and tall windows?",
    answer: "Many Twickenham homes feature 10-12 foot ceilings, tall windows, and impressive chandeliers. We bring proper ladders and equipment to safely clean these features. Our team is trained in working at height and handling delicate fixtures. We'll clean your historic windows, dust high moldings, and carefully detail your chandeliers without risk to your home or our team."
  },
  {
    question: "Can you work with my restoration contractor?",
    answer: "Definitely. Many Twickenham homeowners do careful restoration projects. We're experienced working alongside preservation contractors for post-construction cleanup. We understand the difference between construction dust and historic surfaces, and we'll remove debris while protecting your newly restored features. We can coordinate timing and provide the thorough cleanup your restoration deserves."
  },
  {
    question: "What about homes with mixed historic and modern updates?",
    answer: "Most Twickenham homes blend historic character with modern conveniences - original hardwoods with updated kitchens, antique mantels with central air. We adjust our approach room by room, using appropriate products for each surface. Your updated bathroom gets modern cleaning methods, while your original parlor receives historic-appropriate care. Best of both worlds."
  }
];

