          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Twickenham stands as Alabama's largest antebellum district and one of the most significant historic neighborhoods in the South. Established in 1821, this National Register district contains some of Huntsville's finest architectural treasures - Greek Revival mansions, Federal-style homes, Victorian cottages, and Italianate beauties that have witnessed nearly two centuries of American history.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
            These aren't just old houses; they're irreplaceable pieces of Southern architectural heritage. Current values range from $400,000 to over $1.5 million, reflecting both the historic significance and the meticulous care these properties require. Original heart pine floors, hand-carved mantels, period millwork, wavy glass windows, plaster walls, and architectural details you simply cannot replicate in modern construction.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
            Cleaning a historic Twickenham home isn't like cleaning a new suburban house. These properties demand understanding of preservation principles, knowledge of historic materials, and respect for irreplaceable features. One wrong product can damage original finishes permanently. That's the expertise we bring to every Twickenham property we serve.
          </p>
